INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea1950","letter","1776-11-26","Albany","NY","US","Benedict","Arnold",NULL,"Anthony","Wayne",NULL,"individual",NULL,"The Enemy have taken Fort Washington, (after an obstinate Defence), & made the Garrison, consisting of Near Two Thousand Men Prisoners","ltr_bea1950.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,34,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3000","letter","1775-09-25","Fort Western","ME","US","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","I found the bateaux completed, but many of them smaller than the directions given, and very badly built - of course I have been obliged to order twenty more, to bring on the remainder of the provisions","ltr_bea3000.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,1);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3001","letter","1775-12-05","Quebec City","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","I continued at Point-aux-Trembles until the 3d instant, when, to my great joy, General Montgomery joined us, with artillery, and about three hundred men.","ltr_bea3001.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3002","letter","1776-02-27","Quebec City","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","The enemy, to the number of about five hundred, have twice sallied out at Palace Gate, with design of seizing our field-pieces","ltr_bea3002.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3003","letter","1776-05-08","Montreal","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","I heartily congratulate you on the success of your arms against Boston, and am sorry it is not in my power to give you a more pleasing account of our affairs in this country, which wear no very favorable aspect at present.","ltr_bea3003.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3004","letter","1777-01-13","Providence","RI","US","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","There are, at this place and in the vicinity, about two thousand men, part of six thousand ordered from the New England States. The others are on their march, and expected in, a few days.","ltr_bea3004.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3005","letter","1777-01-31","Providence","RI","US","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","By the best intelligence we have been able to procure of the enemy's force on Rhode Island, it consisted of about six thousand men - eleven regiments of British, and four of Hessians.","ltr_bea3005.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3006","letter","1777-03-11","Providence","RI","US","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","The new levies of the Massachusetts Bay being all ordered to Ticonderoga, and those of Connecticut inoculated for the smallpox, deprives us of the aid of Continental troops, on whom we had placed our chief dependence.","ltr_bea3006.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3007","letter","1777-03-26","Providence","RI","US","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","I was made very unhappy, a few days since, by hearing your Excellency was exceedingly ill with a fever.","ltr_bea3007.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3008","letter","1776-01-14","Quebec City","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","Our loss and repulse struck an amazing panic into both officers and men, and, had the enemy improved their advantage, our affairs here must have been entirely ruined.","ltr_bea3008.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3009","letter","1775-11-08","St Marie","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","Richard","Montgomery","","individual","","I can only say we have hauled our bateaux up over falls, up rapid streams, over carrying-places, and marched through morasses, thick woods, and over mountains, about three hundred and twenty miles","ltr_bea3009.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3010","letter","1775-11-13","Point Levy","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","Richard","Montgomery","","individual","","The winds have been so high, these three nights, that I have not been able to cross the river. I have near forty canoes ready","ltr_bea3010.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3011","letter","1775-11-14","Colvil Place","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","Richard","Montgomery","","individual","","I wrote you yesterday from Point Levy, by an express sent from Sorel, by Colonel Easton, of my intention of crossing the St. Lawrence, which I happily effected between nine and four in the morning","ltr_bea3011.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3012","letter","1775-11-14","Quebec City","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","Hector","Cramahe","","individual","","The unjust, cruel, and tyrannical acts of a venal British Parliament, tending to enslave the American Colonies, have obliged them to appeal to God and the sword for redress.","ltr_bea3012.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3013","letter","1776-11-15","Quebec City","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","Hector","Cramahe","","individual","","This I imputed to the ignorance of your guards, and ordered him to return this morning, and, to my great surprise, he was received in the same manner as yesterday.","ltr_bea3013.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3014","letter","1775-11-16","Quebec City","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","Richard","Montgomery","","individual","","I am very anxious to hear from you, and much more to see you here.","ltr_bea3014.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3015","letter","1775-11-20","Point-aux-Trembles","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","Richard","Montgomery","","individual","","upon examination, great part of our cartridges proved unfit for service, and, to my great surprise, we had no more than five rounds for each man, and near one hundred muskets unfit for service.","ltr_bea3015.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3016","letter","1775-11-20","Point-aux-Trembles","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","It was judged prudent, in our situation, not to hazard a battle, but retire to this place, eight leagues from Quebec, which we did yesterday, and are waiting here with impatience the arrival of General Montgomery","ltr_bea3016.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3017","letter","1775-12-31","","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","David","Wooster","","individual","","I make no doubt but General Montgomery acquainted you with his intentions of storming Quebec as soon as a good opportunity offered.","ltr_bea3017.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3018","letter","1776-01-02","","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","David","Wooster","","individual","","I wrote you, three days since, of our defeat, and the death of General Montgomery and others, with all the information I then had of the matter.","ltr_bea3018.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3019","letter","1776-01-11","Quebec City","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","","","","group","Continental Congress","The disposition of the Canadians is very favorable to your wishes - the only bar of consequence is Quebec. As this is the key, so, in a great measure, it governs the whole country, who having been so long habituated to slavery","ltr_bea3019.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3020","letter","1776-01-12","Quebec City","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","","","","group","Continental Congress","General Wooster has acquainted me he cannot leave Montreal, but has sent down Colonel Clinton, to whom I shall resign the command, until my wound will permit my doing duty","ltr_bea3020.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3021","letter","1776-01-24","Quebec City","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","","","","group","Continental Congress","It is very probable the city would surrender before half, or perhaps one quarter, of the shot, shells, &c. in my memorandum were expended - but, if they should make an obstinate resistance, perhaps the whole will be necessary.","ltr_bea3021.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3022","letter","1776-02-01","Quebec City","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","","","","position","President Of Congress","I have the pleasure of acquainting you, that we still hold our ground before Quebec, and keep the enemy closely blockaded, though we have received but a small reenforcement of one hundred and fifty men from Montreal.","ltr_bea3022.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3023","letter","1776-04-20","Montreal","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","Philip","Schuyler","","individual","","Inclosed is a list of our force before Quebec, which, I am I sorry to say, is so very inconsiderable, and illy supplied with every requisite to carry on a siege, that I am very dubious of their success.","ltr_bea3023.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3024","letter","1776-04-30","Montreal","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","Philip","Schuyler","","individual","","I have the pleasure to acquaint you of the safe arrival of the gentlemen from Congress, in good health and spirits.","ltr_bea3024.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3025","letter","1776-05-15","Sorel","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","","","","group","Commissioners In Canada","I have purchased twenty-seven hundred bushels of wheat of Captain Cuthbert, at four shillings and sixpence, lawful money, payable in our paper bills of exchange, or an order on Congress","ltr_bea3025.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3026","letter","1776-05-17","Sorel","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","","","","group","Commissioners In Canada","I am. very happy to find you are in sentiments with me in respect to the smallpox.","ltr_bea3026.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3027","letter","1776-05-25","Lachine","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","","","","group","Commissioners In Canada","One of our men this moment came in, who was taken at the Cedars. He made his escape this morning, and says we have lost only ten privates killed - the rest are prisoners at St. Ann's and the Cedars.","ltr_bea3027.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3028","letter","1776-05-27","St Ann","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","","","","group","Commissioners In Canada","I had sent early in the morning to the savages, demanding a surrender of our prisoners, and, in case of refusal, and that any of them were murdered, I would sacrifice every Indian who fell into my hands","ltr_bea3028.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3029","letter","1776-06-05","Montreal","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","John","Sullivan","","individual","","I think it absolutely necessary some effectual methods should be taken with the savages immediately, or we shall be obliged to keep up a large force here.","ltr_bea3029.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3030","letter","1776-06-06","Montreal","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","Philip","Schuyler","","individual","","Our want of almost every necessary for the army, and repeated misfortunes and losses, have greatly dispirited the troops. Our enemies are daily increasing, and our friends deserting us.","ltr_bea3030.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3031","letter","1776-06-10","Montreal","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","Philip","Schuyler","","individual","","There was a meeting of those Indians and several other tribes at Caghnawaga, some of whom agreed to deliver up the hatchet received from Governor Carleton last year, and remain neuter in the present dispute.","ltr_bea3031.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3032","letter","1776-06-10","Chamblee","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","John","Sullivan","","individual","","Shall we sacrifice the few men we have, by endeavouring to keep possession of a small part of the country, which can be of little or no service to us ?","ltr_bea3032.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3033","letter","1776-06-13","St Ann","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","Philip","Schuyler","","individual","","We have a report here, that on Sunday last our army, of about two thousand men, under the command of General Thompson, attacked the enemy near Three Rivers, and were repulsed","ltr_bea3033.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3034","letter","1776-06-13","Lachine","QC","CAN","Benedict","Arnold","","Philip","Schuyler","","individual","","Burgoyne is with the enemy. Seventy transports, and, by the best accounts, ten thousand troops, are arrived in Quebec.","ltr_bea3034.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3035","letter","1776-07-30","Ticonderoga","NY","US","Benedict","Arnold","","Philip","Schuyler","","individual","","I left them such directions as I thought necessary, and orders to begin four row-galleys, nearly of the construction of those built in Philadelphia, to carry four pieces heavy and two pieces light cannon each.","ltr_bea3035.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3036","letter","1776-08-08","Skenesborough","NY","US","Benedict","Arnold","","Philip","Schuyler","","individual","","The carpenters go on with great spirit. Eight gondolas will be completed in a few days. One row-galley is gone to Ticonderoga, and will soon be fitted and armed.","ltr_bea3036.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3037","letter","1776-08-31","Button Mould Bay","VT","US","Benedict","Arnold","","Horatio","Gates","","individual","","Inclosed is a return of the strength of the fleet, by which you will observe that seventy-four men are wanting to complete the numbers proposed for the vessels, which are barely sufficient when complete.","ltr_bea3037.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3038","letter","1776-09-02","Willsborough","NY","US","Benedict","Arnold","","Horatio","Gates","","individual","","I have some thoughts of going to Congress, and begging leave to resign. Do you think they will make me a Major-General?","ltr_bea3038.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3039","letter","1776-09-07","Windmill Point","VT","US","Benedict","Arnold","","Horatio","Gates","","individual","","I have posted my guard-boats at a point running into the Lake, about one mile below us. The enemy's boats have several times appeared on the Lake, with a view of decoying our boats","ltr_bea3039.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3040","letter","1776-10-12","Schuylers Island","NY","US","Benedict","Arnold","","Horatio","Gates","","individual","","At half past twelve the engagement became general, and very warm. Some of the enemy's ships, and all their gondolas, beat and rowed up within musket shot of us.","ltr_bea3040.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3041","letter","1776-10-15","Ticonderoga","NY","US","Benedict","Arnold","","Philip","Schuyler","","individual","","They kept up an incessant fire upon us for about five glasses, with round and grape shot, which we returned as briskly. The sails, rigging, and hull of the Congress were shattered and torn in pieces","ltr_bea3041.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3042","letter","1776-10-24","Ticonderoga","NY","US","Benedict","Arnold","","Philip","Schuyler","","individual","","I am extremely glad to hear the militia are coming to our assistance. I believe the enemy, from the best accounts we can collect, are endeavouring to fortify Crown Point.","ltr_bea3042.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3043","letter","1775-10-13","Kennebec River","ME","US","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","The men in general not understanding bateaux, have been obliged to wade, and haul them more than half way up the river.","ltr_bea3043.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3044","letter","1776-06-25","Albany","NY","US","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","By this express you will receive advice from General Schuyler of our evacuating Canada, an event which I make no doubt (from our distressed situation) you have some time expected.","ltr_bea3044.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3045","letter","1777-06-16","Cornells Ferry","PA","US","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","As the militia can be but illy spared at this busy season, I wish to know, as early as possible, your Excellency's orders respecting them - if you wish to have them in the Jerseys or on this side the Delaware.","ltr_bea3045.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3046","letter","1778-06-22","Philadelphia","PA","US","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","Fifty volunteers have engaged to go with General Cadwalader, who this minute informs me he expects to collect a considerable number more in the morning","ltr_bea3046.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,88,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3200","letter","1779-05-05","Philadelphia","PA","US","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","If your Excellency thinks me criminal, for Heaven's sake let me be immediately tried, and, if found guilty, executed. I want no favor - I ask only for justice.","ltr_bea3200.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,73,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3201","letter","1780-03-06","Philadelphia","PA","US","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","From the injury I have received in my leg, and the great stiffness in my ankle, my surgeons are of opinion it will not be prudent for me to take a command in the army for some time to come.","ltr_bea3201.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,73,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3203","letter","1777-08-21","German Flats","NY","US","Benedict","Arnold","","Horatio","Gates","","individual","","I leave this place this morning with twelve hundred Continental troops, officers included, and a handful of militia, for Fort Schuyler, which is still besieged by a number equal to ours.","ltr_bea3203.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,73,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3204","letter","1777-08-23","Fort Dayton","NY","US","Benedict","Arnold","","Horatio","Gates","","individual","","The excessively bad roads, and necessary precautions in marching through a thick wood, retarded us so much, that we have but this moment reached this place","ltr_bea3204.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,73,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3205","letter","1777-08-28","German Flats","NY","US","Benedict","Arnold","","Horatio","Gates","","individual","","You may depend on my joining you as soon as possible with my detachment, about twelve hundred men. Few Indians will be with me.","ltr_bea3205.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,73,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3700","letter","1780-08-06","Robinsons House","NY","US","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","On my arrival at this post, I found every thing thrown into great confusion, by the troops removing from hence, and the militia coming in.","ltr_bea3700.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,59,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3701","letter","1780-08-08","Robinsons House","NY","US","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","I wish your Excellency would be kind enough to order Mr. Erskine to send me a map of the country from this place to New York, particularly on the east side of the river, which would be very useful to me.","ltr_bea3701.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,59,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3702","letter","1780-09-11","Dobbs Ferry","NY","US","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","I came here this morning, in order to establish signals, to be observed in case the enemy came up the river - to give some directions respecting the guard-boats - and to have a beacon fixed upon the mountain","ltr_bea3702.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,59,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3703","letter","1780-09-12","Robinsons House","NY","US","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","The order, contained in the postscript of your Excellency's letter of the 7th, to send the eight bargemen of Colonel Putnam's regiment to join their regiment, I conceive to be on a supposition of their being idle at West Point.","ltr_bea3703.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,59,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3704","letter","1780-09-14","Robinsons House","NY","US","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","I am, therefore, of opinion, that the Pennsylvania line, which I suppose to amount to twenty-five hundred or three thousand men, should hold themselves in readiness to march","ltr_bea3704.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,59,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_bea3705","letter","1780-09-16","Robinsons House","NY","US","Benedict","Arnold","","George","Washington","","individual","","My answers to the questions proposed by your Excellency to the Council of War I will do myself the honor to deliver in person.","ltr_bea3705.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,59,0);
